- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is also likely as the paper focuses on the use of emerging memories as electronic synapses. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses design considerations for implementing neuromorphic architectures. 
- cs.EM (Electronics Materials) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of emerging memories as electronic synapses. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the importance of wire energy in design decisions, which is relevant to hardware implementations of computer vision systems.
